  • Constructor Details

    • RegularManualTransmission

      public RegularManualTransmission(int l1, int h1, int l2, int h2, int l3, int h3, int l4, int h4, int l5, int h5) throws IllegalArgumentException
      This constructor that takes the speed ranges for the 5 gears as two integral numbers each: low and high. The transmission supports exactly 5 gears, numbered 1 through 5. Gear 1 has the lowest speed range.
      Parameters:
      l1 - low speed for gear 1.
      h1 - high speed for gear 1.
      l2 - low speed for gear 2.
      h2 - high speed for gear 2.
      l3 - low speed for gear 3.
      h3 - high speed for gear 3.
      l4 - low speed for gear 4.
      h4 - high speed for gear 4.
      l5 - low speed for gear 5.
      h5 - high speed for gear 5.
      Throws:
      IllegalArgumentException - if for each gear x, lx is greater than hx, the lower speed of x is greater than x+1, and adjacent gears ranges are non-overlapping.
